ce:section.ce:para:
The CDs synthesis was reported in our previous paper [15]. The fabrication of PIn and PIn/CDs was achieved by the hybrid-electrospray technique. 0.01 M PIn was dissolved in 0.01 M nitric acid at 60 °C with constant stirring for 1 h and allowed to cool at room temperature. The various weight percentage of CDs (0.1, 0.2, and 0.3 W%) was added to the PIn solution, then the PIn/CDs solution was sprayed on the conductive substrate by electrospraying deposition (Fig. 1
                        ): applied voltage is 10 kV, the distance between the nozzle and substrate is 2 cm and the rate of PIN/CDs flow is 1.0 ml h−1. The above same method is used to synthesize pristine PIn film without CDs. As synthesized electrodes, pristine PIn, and PIn-CDs (0.1, 0.2, and 0.3 W%)are named PIn, PCDs-1, PCDs-2, and PCDs-3.The mole ratio of PIn and CDs and the active materials mass loading is listed in Table 1
                        .
